text.tspan: This is a story about Johnny discovering a vulnerability in an enterprise product.
A DR failover solution is part of a fire safety plan migrating a critical database to
a backup office across the street. The DR process involves shutting down all
services and unmounting storage before remounting storage and activating
services in the backup DC. If the storage can't be unmounted within 10 seconds
the active node is STONITHed via power disconnect, which will likely corrupt the
database. During testing failover verifies that processes have no open file
handles in /proc/*/fd but storage still fails to unmount and the testd database is
corrupted. A DBA is running monitoring applications on the same node with
LD_LIBRARY_PATH set to a path in the shared storage.
Winner gets an OrangePi Zero 3 loaded with Llama.
